## Summary

This study evaluated perceptual and motor characteristics in a child-like bodily experience created using a body-transformation suit. The work examined how changing bodily conditions can alter perception and movement during interaction with the environment.

The study contributes to the Measuring and HCI lines by experimentally arranging bodily and perceptual conditions and evaluating their effects on human experience and movement. It also provides a basis for later work on egocentric smaller-person experiences through changes in visual perspective.

## Research line

- **Measuring**: evaluation of perceptual and motor changes under altered bodily conditions
- **HCI**: embodied interaction and body-transformation interfaces
- **Embodied Interaction**: changing body–environment relations through wearable systems

